column2: Greenhornet, 75 or over on Treatment for 10 years or more (Patient)
column9: I have tken the gernic of Darvocet for 10 years plus.I have found no serious side effect(read on). Dosage perscribed is one every 4 hrs but I have never taken more than 2 p/day(because they were so effective) until this last yr and now take 3 p/day.It is not as effective as it was the first 5 yrs. In the beginning it gave me a real lift as it was very effective.I found when working and under stress I was taking it for the lift as much as for pain. I stopped that immediately when I realized that. Now 6 years later and retired I have much more pain in the hips and three a day is hardly adequate but I am concerned with taking to many drugs. I realize that for effect I need to take 1 evry four hours thru the day but no more than 3 p/day.Dr. says I can take more if needed. MY brother has same kind of pain in the hips and he say's they are not effective in reducing his pain.No help at all. I insist they must be a little help but he say's he does not realize he has even taken one. I think you need to take one every four hours for 12 hours to realize if they are of benefit. I do note the side effect that perhaps I may get a little impatient(close to anger which I surpress) at times and perhaps talk a little more than normal.
